{
  "texts": [
    "This selection process also involved excluding side branches such as obtuse marginal and diagonals that appear infrequently and suffer from limited visibility within the dataset 36.",
    "Such exclusions help avoid inaccuracies in segmentation and simplify the analysis of the LCA, as these rarely segmented branches can hinder the generalizability and performance of the segmentation model model.",
    "36 This algorithm was developed by testing, over 200 epochs, nine state-of-the-art segmentation models, i.e.",
    "UNet 39, UNet+ + 40, MANet 41, LinkNet 42, FPN 43, PSPNet 44, DeepLabV3 45, DeepLabV3+ 46 and PAN 47, and five loss functions, i.e.",
    "Jaccard loss, Dice loss, focal loss, Lovasz loss and Tversky loss."
  ]
}